# Angular Setup Guide (Windows)

A complete step-by-step guide to install Angular, create a project, and run it locally using VS Code.

---

## Prerequisites

* Windows 10/11
* Internet Connection
* VS Code
* Node.js (LTS Version)

---

## Step 1: Install Node.js

Download and install the LTS version from:

https://nodejs.org

Verify the installation:

```bash
node -v
npm -v
```

---

## Step 2: Install Angular CLI

```bash
npm install -g @angular/cli
```

Verify the installation:

```bash
ng version
```

---

## Step 3: Create a New Angular Project

```bash
ng new my-angular-app
```

Choose the desired options:

* CSS or SCSS
* SSR: No (for beginners)

---

## Step 4: Open the Project

```bash
cd my-angular-app
code .
```

---

## Step 5: Run the Application

```bash
ng serve
```

or

```bash
ng serve --open
```

Open your browser:

```
http://localhost:4200
```

---

# Angular CLI Commands

## Check Angular Version

```bash
ng version
```

---

## Create Component

```bash
ng generate component component-name
```

Shortcut:

```bash
ng g c component-name
```

Example:

```bash
ng g c home
```

---

## Create Service

```bash
ng generate service services/user
```

Shortcut:

```bash
ng g s services/user
```

---

## Create Module

```bash
ng g m admin
```

---

## Create Pipe

```bash
ng g p pipes/search
```

---

## Create Directive

```bash
ng g d directives/highlight
```

---

## Create Guard

```bash
ng g guard guards/auth
```

---

## Create Interface

```bash
ng g interface models/user
```

---

## Create Class

```bash
ng g class models/student
```

---

## Create Enum

```bash
ng g enum models/role
```

---

## Build the Project

Development Build:

```bash
ng build
```

Production Build:

```bash
ng build --configuration production
```

---

## Run Tests

```bash
ng test
```

---

## Update Angular

```bash
ng update
```

Update Angular CLI:

```bash
npm install -g @angular/cli@latest
```

---

## Install Packages

Example:

```bash
npm install bootstrap
npm install axios
npm install lodash
```

---

## Uninstall Package

```bash
npm uninstall bootstrap
```

---

## View Installed Packages

```bash
npm list
```

---

## Clean npm Cache

```bash
npm cache clean --force
```

---

## Reinstall Dependencies

Delete `node_modules` and `package-lock.json`, then run:

```bash
npm install
```

---

## Stop Development Server

Press:

```
Ctrl + C
```

